u &quot;jam&quot; your mouse fast left to really get to the spell you need to cast fast, and your mouse is not interfering with the center area data you need to see, and the buffs junks is high right out of your way.<br><br>You can tell this is a person who has lots of hours on their toon. <br><br>Still Up is better against most mobs though. <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/usamdeathwalker.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Sam DeathWalker</A> at: 7/30/02 8:58:18 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uloral.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Loral</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(7/31/02 2:48:53 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm41.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=159.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://loralciriclight.com/images/loral_face_60x60.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Single box for Target, Player and Group info</span><hr size=1> 190 days to be exact.<br><br>One thing about the user interface, regardless of look.  If you are using a mouse to click in stuff, it is too slow.  Hotkey hotkey hotkey.  Alt+number for spell, Number key for hotbox.  Q to attack, Z for spellbook, Shift + QWERT to switch targeting group members.<br><br>With the frame rate drop in higher end raids, you HAVE to be faster than mousing around, clicking a guy and clicking a button.  Hotkeys...learn em, live em, love em.<br><br>Because of this you can also strip out a lot of stuff out of the UI.  I generally keep the UI to just necessary information. <p><a href="http://loralciriclight.com/"><img src="http://loralciriclight.com/images/loral_dragon_sig.jpg" border="0" alt="Loral's Signature" height="132" width="302"></a><br /><a href="http://loralciriclight.com/loral.html">bio</a> - <a href="htt